10/09/2006
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- Police announced on Sunday (10 September) that they have detained 20 people suspected of organised crime and of planning terrorist acts. 
The suspects were arrested in Tuzi and Malesije on Saturday after several months of surveillance. 
According to the authorities, a large stash of weapons, explosives and drugs was seized during the operation, which was conducted in co-operation with Albanian security services. 
The group may have active cells in Albania and Kosovo, police said. 
(B92, Mina - 10/09/06)
